{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"470d0119-ea8f-4751-829d-baad2f6d1abd","content":"No repo-specific docs here, but here's the recommended MSTest setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` bundles the runner, framework, and analyzers — no extra `<PackageReference>` needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution (`.runsettings`)\n\nCreate a file at the project root:\n\n```xml\n<!-- tests.runsettings -->\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>        <!-- 0 = use all logical CPUs -->\n      <Scope>MethodLevel</Scope>  <!-- parallelize across methods -->\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nThen reference it in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\tests.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nUse `[DoNotParallelize]` on a test class:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nAll methods in that class will run sequentially **and** wait until no other parallel tests are executing.\n\n**Key points:**\n- **`Workers=0`** — scales to available CPUs automatically.\n- **`Scope=MethodLevel`** — maximum parallelism (use `ClassLevel` if tests share per-class state).\n- **`[DoNotParallelize]`** — opt specific classes out; can also be applied per-method or at assembly level.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ecddba53-2c41-40fd-b273-8a5b46cc6c2a","outputTokens":501,"requestId":"603F:220345:2485DAA:272E805:6A03127E"},"id":"7bb65a27-be3b-442f-8e66-2fae4fdc9e4a","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:44:11.910Z","parentId":"e1512cef-4b28-4208-8d5d-6e24e65743a6"}
